        <updateDate>2009-07-20T20:22:00Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Fair Treatment for Precious Metals Investors Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to treat bullion (e.g., gold, silver, platinum, and palladium) as a long-term capital asset (currently, treated as a collectible), eligible for preferential capital gains tax rates. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Fair Treatment for Precious Metals Investors Act</title>
    <titles>
      <item>
        <titleType>Display Title</titleType>
        <title>Fair Treatment for Precious Metals Investors Act</title>
      </item>
      <item>
        <titleType>Official Title as Introduced</titleType>
        <title>A bill to amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to treat gold, silver, platinum, and palladium, in either coin or bar form, in the same manner as equities and mutual funds for purposes of the maximum capital gains rate for individuals.</title>
        <billTextVersionName>Introduced in Senate</billTextVersionName>
        <billTextVersionCode>IS</billTextVersionCode>
      </item>
